Definition: an oppressive quality that is laborious and solemn and lacks grace or fluency
Example: a book so serious that it sometimes subsided into ponderousness; his lectures tend to heaviness and repetition
Synonyms: adj, all, uninteresting, ponderous, heaviness, dull, heavy, uninterestingness, an, oppressive, quality, that, is, laborious, and, solemn, lacks, grace, or, fluency, a, book, so, serious, it, sometimes, subsided, into, his, lectures, tend, to, repetition
Category: noun.attribute
